Ronan Farrow, the estranged son of Woody Allen, has penned an op-ed slamming both his filmmaker father as well as the media for not devoting as much press to the director’s alleged sexual abuse as they do to his new films.
In that piece, the allegations of sexual abuse levied on Allen by his daughter Dylan Farrow were never broached in the interview and limited to a parenthetical aside within the story itself.
“I believe my sister,” Ronan wrote of Dylan’s sexual abuse claims against Allen.
“Very often, women with allegations do not or cannot bring charges,” Farrow wrote.
Sometimes, we’re the only ones who can play that role.”In the case of both Cosby and Allen, Farrow writes, “The allegations were never backed by a criminal conviction.